</Fleet><?xml version="1.0"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>Black Wing</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>KUIPER/kuiper</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=yellow&gt;MODERATE&lt;/color&gt;

Black Wing "Silencers" is a wing centered around Ambush Tactics, Map Control, and Reconnaissance.
Composed of five Particle Lance destroyers, and two long-range spotter corvettes equipped with pulse generators.
Operating in the shadows, the goal of the fleet is to lock down and control as wide a region of space as possible with distributed forces. Punishing movement with swift ambush from a net of cross-firing beams. Leverage intelligence to make informed decisions, pre-aim ambushes, and remain detected as little as possible; creeping up on an enemy battle-line and preying on any exposed assets.

Notes:
-It is suggested to operate the destroyers in Radar Off and Comms Recieve Only, relying on the spotters to pass tracks to the destroyers which can subsequently lock even with the search of their radars off. This is done to reduce the detectability of the destroyers to long-range radar that would otherwise ruin an ambush.
-The Kyves are equipped with burnthrough pulse generators giving the ships a surefire way to detect stealthy assets.
-While the beams excel at up-front damage, care must be taken. Unlike the MK600 beam, the Particle Lance is unable to BSHORT and though the damage is significant, it is finite and the beam ships are fragile.  
  </Description>
